edu.uml.cs.isense.dfm
Class FieldMatching

java.lang.Object
  Activity
      edu.uml.cs.isense.dfm.FieldMatching

public class FieldMatching
extends Activity

The FieldMatching class lists off fields from a project, which the implementor must pass in as an intent extra to DFM_ORDER_LIST, and makes a best attempt of matching them with known field names in the system. It provides drop-down menus for users to reconfigure fields they would like to record for this project. When this activity finishes, fields accepted by the user are stored in the acceptedFields LinkedList, which is public for any implementation to grab.

Field Detail

DFM_ORDER_LIST

public static final java.lang.String DFM_ORDER_LIST
The hard-coded String key that the implementor should pair with a String[] of their DataFieldManager instance's order array. Please note this must be a String[], but DFM's order field is a LinkedList. See convertOrderToStringArray() to easily convert order into a String[].

Constant Field Values

acceptedFields

public static java.util.LinkedList<java.lang.String> acceptedFields
The list of fields the user accepts with. In other words, it will be a list of all the fields selected in the drop-down menus.

compatible

public static boolean compatible
A public boolean that can be checked upon return of this activity to see if the project was compatible with the app or not. A typical implementation would ask the user to select a new project and launch the FieldMatching activity again with that new project.

SHOULD_BUILD_PREFS_STRING

public static java.lang.String SHOULD_BUILD_PREFS_STRING
This hardcoded String is used to identify whether or not the FieldMatching class should build a String containing accepted fields in SharedPreferences.
